  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">1</span> What You're Consenting To</h2>
    <p>By checking the SMS consent box on a form at <strong>406frontdesk.com</strong>, you agree to receive SMS text messages from <strong>406 Front Desk</strong> (operated by 406 Front Desk LLC). Checking the box is optional and separate from submitting the form. These messages may include:</p>
    <div class="highlight-card">
      <div class="msg-row"><span class="msg-icon" aria-hidden="true">📅</span><div><strong>Appointment reminders</strong> and booking confirmations</div></div>
      <div class="msg-row"><span class="msg-icon" aria-hidden="true">📲</span><div><strong>Missed call follow-ups</strong> — so you never lose a lead</div></div>
      <div class="msg-row"><span class="msg-icon" aria-hidden="true">💬</span><div><strong>AI receptionist responses</strong> to your inquiries</div></div>
      <div class="msg-row"><span class="msg-icon" aria-hidden="true">🔔</span><div><strong>Service notifications</strong> relevant to your account or demo request</div></div>
      <div class="msg-row"><span class="msg-icon" aria-hidden="true">🎁</span><div><strong>Promotional offers</strong> — only if you've separately opted in to marketing messages</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 2 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">2</span> How We Collect Consent</h2>
    <p>Consent is collected explicitly through a <strong>separate, optional, unchecked-by-default SMS-consent checkbox</strong> on a web form at <strong>406frontdesk.com</strong>. Only checking that box opts you in to receive SMS messages from 406 Front Desk — entering your phone number or submitting the form does not. Consent is never required as a condition of purchase or service.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 3 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">3</span> Message Frequency</h2>
    <p>Message frequency varies depending on your activity and the services being used. For demo requests, you can expect <strong>1–3 messages</strong> during the demo session. For ongoing service clients, frequency will vary based on appointment activity and business needs.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 4 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">4</span> How to Opt Out</h2>
    <p>You can opt out of SMS messages at any time using any of the following methods:</p>
    <ul class="opt-out-list">
      <li><span class="badge">TEXT</span> Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message you receive from us — you will be immediately unsubscribed.</li>
      <li><span class="badge">TEXT</span> Reply <strong>CANCEL</strong> or <strong>UNSUBSCRIBE</strong> — these also remove you from our list.</li>
      <li><span class="badge">EMAIL</span> Contact us directly at <a href="mailto:admin@406frontdesk.com">admin@406frontdesk.com</a> to request removal.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 5 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">5</span> Help &amp; Support</h2>
    <p>Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message for assistance, or contact us directly at <a href="mailto:admin@406frontdesk.com">admin@406frontdesk.com</a> or by phone or text at <a href="tel:+14068400404">(406) 840-0404</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 6 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">6</span> Your Privacy</h2>
    <p>Your phone number and personal information are <strong>never sold, rented, or shared</strong> with third parties for marketing purposes. Information is used solely to deliver the AI receptionist service and communications you've requested. For full details, see our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/terms-conditions/">Terms of Service</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 7 -->
  <div class="policy-section">
    <h2><span class="num">7</span> Messaging Rates</h2>
    <p>Standard message and data rates may apply depending on your mobile carrier and plan. 406 Front Desk does not charge for SMS messages, but your carrier may.</p>
